intro: Tarenna depauperata, commonly known as the slender tarenna, is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is native to Madagascar and is characterized by its small, simple leaves and clusters of small, white flowers. The plant typically grows as a shrub or small tree, often found in humid, tropical environments. Its fruit is a small, dry capsule that contains several seeds. Tarenna depauperata is of interest to botanists due to its unique morphology and potential ecological role in its native habitat.
